    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - FULLER 10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS - SPECIAL PROCEDURES</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>SPECIAL PROCEDURES</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="5">
            <title>INPUT SHAFT (WITHOUT MAIN CASE DISASSEMBLY)</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303207">Figure 7</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1303207" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg13/g1303207.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 7. Input Shaft Assembly</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>The Eaton Fuller transmission is designed so that the input shaft can be replaced without
                disassembling the transmission.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the shift bar housing according to SHIFT BAR HOUSING,
                    <hotlnk document="s13032_40.xml" xrefid="x1303201">Remove</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the clutch housing according to CLUTCH HOUSING,
                    <hotlnk document="s13032_42.xml" xrefid="x1303202">Remove</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the six (6) bolts from the input bearing cover, and remove the bearing cover (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1303208">Figure 8</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1303208" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg13/g1303208.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 8. Remove Input Bearing Cover</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If present, remove and discard the rubber seal ring on the input shaft.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">From the input shaft groove, remove the input bearing retaining snap ring.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>If the input shaft is moved rearward too far, damage to the input shaft clutching teeth can
                        occur.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With a soft mallet, move the input shaft
                    <emph type="bold">slightly</emph>
                    rearward (approximately 1/16 inch) until
                    <emph type="bold">resistance is felt.</emph>
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Grasp input shaft, wiggle it, and pull it forward to move the input bearing forward and
                    expose the snap ring on the outside of the input bearing (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1303209">Figure 9</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1303209" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg13/g1303209.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 9. Pull Input Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the bearing puller as shown. Remove the input bearing from the case and input
                    shaft (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1303210">Figure 10</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1303210" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg13/g1303210.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 10. Remove Input Bearing And Input Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the snap ring on the inside of the main drive gear (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1303211">Figure 11</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the input shaft (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1303211">Figure 11</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1303211" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg13/g1303211.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 11. Remove The Snap Ring And Input Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
